            <thetext>This is a placeholder bug for all the disk full conditions.  All our internal file formats need to fail safely if the disk is full - aborting rather than corrupting.

This includes:

* cyrusdb: at least twoskip and flat, hopefully the others will be retired
* cyrus.index/cyrus.cache (even cyrus.squat!)
* quota files - at least don&apos;t lose the quota limits, even if usage can&apos;t be
  reliably captured.</thetext>
